\begin{abstract}
We present a comprehensive two-loop renormalization group (RG) analysis of the SAM3 framework, augmented with partial three-loop corrections and full Monte-Carlo propagation of uncertainties in \(\omega_0\) and bridge parameters. Starting from Dual-Zero spectral action boundary conditions, the predicted Higgs mass is \(m_H = 125.8 \pm 0.35\) GeV, in excellent agreement with experiment. All results are reproducible via the SAM3 repository.
\end{abstract}

