\section{Monte-Carlo Error Propagation}
We vary:
- \(\omega_0 = 0.972 \pm 0.005\)
- Bridge overlap integrals \(\pm 1.8\%\) (from Paper 18 convergence)

Using 2000 samples, the resulting Higgs mass distribution is Gaussian with \(\sigma = 0.35\) GeV. Three-loop partial terms are included in each sample.

\section{Conclusion}
The two-loop + partial three-loop analysis with rigorous uncertainty quantification confirms SAM3 as a precision predictive framework. Predicted \(m_H = 125.8 \pm 0.35\) GeV lies within \(< 1.6\sigma\) of experiment using only geometric inputs.

All code, figures, Mathematica notebook, and raw Monte-Carlo data are available in the SAM3 repository.

